                                            Some developers put too little focus on the widget after making great apps.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Widgets give you a quick look at important information, let you control apps easily, and generally make your Android home screen a much better place. Unfortunately, the reality of Android widgets doesn't always live up to that promise.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 14:00:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/10-great-android-apps-with-bad-widgets/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Is Why The iPhone 17 Pro Is Scratching So Much]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-the-iphone-17-pro-is-scratching-so-much/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-17-pro-2.jpeg" length="220" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The return to aluminum unibodies could've gone better.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple's iPhone 17 Pro series marked the company's return to aluminum unibody builds on their phones after around 8 years of continuous glass sandwiches. But it's also a controversial one—it's scratching a little too easily. Thanks to iFixit, we might know the possible reason behind this.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 13:01:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-the-iphone-17-pro-is-scratching-so-much/</guid></item></channel>
